### Expected Performance Impact

**Theoretical speedup:** 30-50x (with 64 cores, minus coordination overhead)
- Baseline: ~428 ms (scan_filter only)
- Expected after optimization: **8-15 ms** (scan_filter component)
- Total estimated time: **~40-60 ms** (down from ~501 ms)

**Rationale:**
- Load balancing with dynamic scheduling ensures all 64 cores remain busy
- Thread-local aggregation eliminates lock contention (bottleneck on >8 cores)
- Memory bandwidth scales near-linearly for sequential scan workloads
- Merge phase is negligible (only 6 aggregates × 64 threads = 384 operations)

